post_text: On Friday, October 26th the East End Hispanic Heritage Committee had a Hispanic Heritage Museum Walk for students in grades 2 through 4. The objective of each walk was aligned with an ELA, Social Studies, Art, and/or Music learning standard and exposed students to stories, dances, and tales of immigration to the USA. The kindergarten and first grade Dual Language classes also had a morning feast with foods from the Central and South American countries. Thank you to the amazing parents and staff members who prepared such delicious foods and volunteered to help with this event!

When: Saturday, November 17th 2018
7:00 AM - 5:00 PM

Event Details:
NPHS will be hosting its 4th annual robotics event. This year, we are hosting an in-season qualifying event for teams to advance to the state championships. The Student councils will be selling breakfast and lunch to the participants as a fundraiser. We are in need of volunteers to help out that day either in the cafeteria or as event staff. We are also in need of securing food donations in order to feed the expected 300+ attendees.

For more information on the organization visit
https://www.firstinspires.org/robotics/fll
